<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_UI_Camera" s="74219">
  <T n="category">10175<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SimLife--></T>
  <T n="name">0x4F2DF893<!--String: "Camera Controls"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Camera_Controls_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:bde312d0ca8721c1</T>
      <E n="platform_filter">DESKTOP_ONLY</E>
      <T n="text">0xF42A5D23<!--String: "Taking Screenshots and Video in the Sims 4 has never been easier. Simply click the shutter button found next to the time controls."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Camera_Controls_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:bde312d0ca8721c2</T>
      <E n="platform_filter">DESKTOP_ONLY</E>
      <T n="text">0xC284752B<!--String: "Press the camera button (or press C) to take a screenshot of the game. Press the video button (or press V) to start/stop video capture. Click the picture button to view all the screenshots and memories that have been captured."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Camera_Controls_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:bde312d0ca8721c3</T>
      <E n="platform_filter">DESKTOP_ONLY</E>
      <T n="text">0xBA64E666<!--String: "Sims 4 has two camera styles. The default style allows you to click on open terrain and drag to move the camera.\n\nBoth camera styles behave differently, so experiment with the left, right, and middle mouse buttons to find one that suits your play style.\n\nYou can modify the camera style by pressing the Sims 3 / Sims 4 camera buttons at the top right of the screen, press Ctrl+Shift+Tab, or access the Game Camera settings in Game Options."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Camera_Controls_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:bde312d0ca8721c4</T>
      <E n="platform_filter">DESKTOP_ONLY</E>
      <T n="text">0x6812E6DB<!--String: "The default camera style does not have the option to Pitch (or Tilt) the camera. As you zoom the camera in and out, it moves along a path that allows for an easier experience for viewing your Sims.\n\nYou can modify this setting in the Game Options / Controls & Camera tab."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <T n="ui_sort_order">28</T>
</I>